"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jzh1704452873460.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jzh1704452873460.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jzh1704452873460.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hpq1665702837993\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      DTD Objects\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hpq1665702837993__dtd_objects_37472\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Uniface DTD object defines a Uniface-compliant Document Type Definition (DTD), which defines the structure of an XML stream that is used to transfer data between components. It also includes a default mapping from the elements defined in the DTD to Uniface entities and fields.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hpq1665702837993__p_d10820e1_d10821e1_d10822e1\">Uniface-compliant DTDs are used by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">xmlsave</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">xmlload</span> when reading and writing XML parameters. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"moe1665702758445.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/moe1665702758445.html\" title=\"Declarative XML handling is a simple way to write and read XML streams using Uniface-compliant DTDs, element-to-field mappings, and the xmlsave and xmlload ProcScript statements.\">Declarative XML Handling</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hpq1665702837993__p_d10823e1_d10824e1_d10825e1\">You can define DTDs and default mappings to Uniface data using the DTD Editor. It enables you to generate DTDs based on modeled entities and components, import DTD definitions from a file, and map elements in a DTD to Uniface entities and fields.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hpq1665702837993__p_d10826e1_d10827e1_d10828e1\">Compiling a DTD generates a compiled <span class=\"ph filepath\">.dtd</span> file in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">/resources/dtd</code> directory. If the File Name property is defined, it also generates a text file with a <span class=\"ph filepath\">.dtd</span> file extension.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uab1665702654218.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface-Compliant DTDs</a><p>A Document Type Definition (DTD) defines rules for the structure of an XML stream. In Uniface, a DTD is a development object that includes DTD definitions and a default mapping between the XML elements defined by the DTD and Uniface component fields and entities. It can be used to define the rules for the structure of an XML stream that is exchanged between components.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qkw1665702654897.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Working with DTDs</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zox1665702797076.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>DTD Editor</a><p>The DTD Editor allows you to load, create, or edit Document Type Definitions (DTDs) for XML data, and map them to Uniface entities and fields.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5754341\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5754341\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "DTD Objects Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 DTD Objects A Uniface DTD object defines a Uniface-compliant Document Type Definition (DTD), which defines the structure of an XML stream that is used to transfer data between components. It also includes a default mapping from the elements defined in the DTD to Uniface entities and fields. Uniface-compliant DTDs are used by xmlsave and xmlload when reading and writing XML parameters. For more information, see Declarative XML Handling . You can define DTDs and default mappings to Uniface data using the DTD Editor. It enables you to generate DTDs based on modeled entities and components, import DTD definitions from a file, and map elements in a DTD to Uniface entities and fields. Compiling a DTD generates a compiled .dtd file in the /resources/dtd directory. If the File Name property is defined, it also generates a text file with a .dtd file extension. Related Links Uniface-Compliant DTDs A Document Type Definition (DTD) defines rules for the structure of an XML stream. In Uniface, a DTD is a development object that includes DTD definitions and a default mapping between the XML elements defined by the DTD and Uniface component fields and entities. It can be used to define the rules for the structure of an XML stream that is exchanged between components. Working with DTDs DTD Editor The DTD Editor allows you to load, create, or edit Document Type Definitions (DTDs) for XML data, and map them to Uniface entities and fields. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}